Reinforcement Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Reinforcement Learning is the main focus of the paper, as the authors present two algorithms that perform input generalization to address the challenges of credit assignment and uncertainty in mobile robot learning. 

Probabilistic Methods are also mentioned as a complicating factor in the learning problem, due to noisy sensors and effectors in complex dynamic environments. The algorithms presented in the paper trade off long-term optimality for immediate performance and flexibility, which suggests a probabilistic approach to decision-making.
